This paper proposes a CNN architecture for semantic image segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a new module that can be inserted into existing CNN architectures, which involves learning parameters using backpropagation techniques, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of superpixels and edge information, which could potentially fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
